ict should not be overruled by weak\n   913→   913→  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate only\n   914→   914→  // if it has a meaningful positive raw score (avoids ingredient-list leakage).\n   915→   915→  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n   916→   916→    const fallback = scored\n   917→   917→      .slice()\n   918→   918→      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n   919→   919→    if (fallback[0].rawScore > 0.02) {\n   920→   920→      selected = [fallback[0]];\n   921→   921→    }\n   922→   922→  }\n   923→   923→\n   924→   924→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n   925→   925→  // the threshold. Cases:\n   926→   926→  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n   927→   927→  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n   928→   928→  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n   929→   929→  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n   930→   930→  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n   931→   931→  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n   932→   932→    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   933→   933→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   934→   934→      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n   935→   935→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   936→   936→      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n   937→   937→      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   938→   938→    });\n   939→   939→  }\n   940→   940→\n   941→   941→  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join (2-line or 3-line) survived the threshold\n   942→   942→  // and its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix/suffix\n   943→   943→  // so the dedup \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n   944→   944→  // Note: the pre-merge step above already handles the common Baked Eggs case (&/continuation\n   945→   945→  // on next line) by turning it into a single candidate — this block covers the rarer case where\n   946→   946→  // a continuation-character join was generated as a 2-line/3-line candidate and the prefix\n   947→   947→  // single also survived threshold independently (e.g. from a different code path or OCR layout).\n   948→   948→  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n   949→   949→  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   950→   950→  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   951→   951→  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n   952→   952→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   953→   953→      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n   954→   954→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   955→   955→      // Remove PREFIX singles whose continuation join also survived\n   956→   956→      const isPrefixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   957→   957→        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   958→   958→        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n   959→   959→        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7698028